Sandoval County Food pantry. The FSIP Food Distribution Program is a federal program that provides commodity foods to low-income households residing in approved areas in New Mexico.  The Food Distribution Program serves the following approved areas:  Jemez, Cochiti, Santa Ana, Sandia,  and Zia, Santo Domingo, San Felipe and Isleta Pueblos. To be eligible to participate, the household must contain at least one person who is a member of a federally-recognized tribe.WHERE TO APPLYProgram staff is available at the distribution sites and at the main office to certify and distribute. You can visit our website and download the applications by clicking on the link to the .pdfs. Application forms can also be requested by phone, mail, or at the main office. Households may file an application on the same day they contact the Food Distribution Program.  A monthly schedule provides the date(s) and time(s) of each tailgate and warehouse distribution.  Schedules are posted at all distribution sites such as the Tribal Governor's Office, Post Office, and Elderly Centers.  For more information, please call.Office HoursMonday through Friday7:30 am to 4:30pm   Closed from 12:00 noon to 1:00 pm for lunch.
